What are Gas Engines?
Gas engines are internal combustion engines that operate on gaseous fuels such as natural gas, biogas, landfill gas, and syngas. These engines are known for their high efficiency, operational flexibility, and significantly lower emissions compared to diesel or gasoline alternatives. They serve as crucial assets for power generation, mechanical drive applications, and combined heat and power (CHP) systems, playing a vital role in both grid stability and industrial energy solutions.
